title: Section IV's best keep rolling
text:
Section IV's best keep rolling 
By wbng sports October 10, 2015 Updated Oct 10, 2015 at 12:08 AM EDT 
(WBNG Binghamton) Three Section IV teams ranked top six in the latest state rankings continued to cruise with wins on Friday night. 
Maine-Endwell 62 - Corcoran 24: In Syracuse, Maine-Endwell won its 57th consecutive game with a 62-24 victory over Section III's Corcoran. The Spartans own the longest unbeaten streak in New York State history. 
WBNG E-News - Sign Up For Our Newsletter! 
Deposit/Hancock 36 - Bainbridge-Guilford 0: The fourth-ranked team in Class D, Deposit/Hancock, pitched another shutout on Friday at home. The Eagles rolled to a 36-0 win to stay unbeaten on the season. 
Tioga 52 - Sidney 13: Tioga improved to 5-1 with a 52-13 win at Sidney. The Tigers have now won two in a row after losing to Newark Valley a few weeks ago. 
Other Section IV football scores: Johnson City 30 - Horseheads 13Harpursville/Afton 28 - Candor 6Edison 14 - Whitney Point 6Norwich 13 - Dryden 0
